To expand further upon my post:
Furries, which in these threads are often called "anthros". What are they? They behave like humans, think like humans, and live like humans. They look like humans, except with fur taped on. (tails and ears too) So, in most respects, furries are humans, with a few animal traits bound on.

What would an anthropomorphic animal be? It'd be something closer to an animal than a human. For me, examples of anthropomorphic animals are the talking animals of folklore and myth. Even those often have human thought processes, but at least their bodies are visibly non-human.
It's just words. "Furry" is shorter than saying "zoomorph" so I use the former.
